<br>
First, I think the value of emergency mana is fairly good, considering the potential applications.  Ever since mod rod one I have praised that last bit of mana when everyone is shouting oom and i go *click* &quot;not me, one cast left&quot;.  Thus, new rods fill that roll well, both mr1 and mr2.<br>
<br>
Second, the mana regeneration aspect on these is not bad.  You just have to be concious to use them frequently.  With old ones it was tempting to cast and click rapidly, I find that making me wait tends to turn it into more of a regen and less of a burst of mana.  Not good or bad, just different.<br>
<br>
Third, I agree we need a message.  I am thinking something along the bard mana regen song in that it has no icon but gives you a message.  Something like &quot;you experience a transvergeance&quot; is given when you click it ... something like &quot;your transvergeance has ended&quot; should be given when it wears off.  No icon or timer or anything, just a message to let you know when its over.  And are there any other spells with a duration of 5 min that could be used to track this?  Burnout and ds are all too long I think...<br>
